allowPinchZoom.description: Handle zoom or pinch gestures on iOS devices when scroll locking is enabled.

blockScrollOnMount.description: If `true`, scrolling will be disabled on the `body` when the drawer opens.

body.type: string | number | bigint | boolean | ReactElement<unknown, string | JSXElementConstructor<any>> | Iterable<ReactNode> | ReactPortal | Promise<...> | DrawerBodyProps

cancel.type: string | number | bigint | boolean | ReactElement<unknown, string | JSXElementConstructor<any>> | Iterable<ReactNode> | ReactPortal | Promise<...> | ButtonProps
cancel.description: The drawer cancel button to use.

closeOnDrag.description: If `true`, then the drawer will close on drag.

closeOnEsc.description: If `true`, the modal will close when the `Esc` key is pressed.

closeOnOverlay.description: If `true`, the modal will close when the overlay is clicked.

defaultOpen.description: If `true`, the element will be initially opened.

dragConstraints.description: Applies constraints on the permitted draggable area.

dragElastic.description: The degree of movement allowed outside constraints. 0 = no movement, 1 = full movement.

dragOffset.description: Offset from being dragged to closing.

dragVelocity.description: Velocity of the drag that triggers close.

finalFocusRef.description: `ref` of the element to return focus to when `FocusLock` unmounts.

footer.type: string | number | bigint | boolean | ReactElement<unknown, string | JSXElementConstructor<any>> | Iterable<ReactNode> | ReactPortal | Promise<...> | DrawerFooterProps

header.type: string | number | bigint | boolean | ReactElement<unknown, string | JSXElementConstructor<any>> | Iterable<ReactNode> | ReactPortal | Promise<...> | DrawerHeaderProps

initialFocusRef.description: `ref` of the element to receive focus initially.

lockFocusAcrossFrames.description:
Enables aggressive focus capturing within iframes.

- If `true`: keep focus in the lock, no matter where lock is active.
- If `false`: allows focus to move outside of iframe.

middle.type: string | number | bigint | boolean | ReactElement<unknown, string | JSXElementConstructor<any>> | Iterable<ReactNode> | ReactPortal | Promise<...> | ButtonProps
middle.description: The drawer middle button to use.

onCancel.description: The callback invoked when cancel button clicked.

onClose.description: Callback invoked to close the element.

onCloseComplete.description: Callback function to run side effects after the drawer has closed.

onEsc.description: Callback invoked when the escape key is pressed and focus is within modal.

onMiddle.description: The callback invoked when middle button clicked.

onOpen.description: Callback invoked to open the element.

onSuccess.description: The callback invoked when success button clicked.

open.description: If `true`, the element will be opened.

portalProps.description: Props to be forwarded to the portal component.

restoreFocus.description: If `true`, focus will be restored to the element that triggered the `FocusLock` once it unmounts.

success.type: string | number | bigint | boolean | ReactElement<unknown, string | JSXElementConstructor<any>> | Iterable<ReactNode> | ReactPortal | Promise<...> | ButtonProps
success.description: The drawer success button to use.

timing.description: The timing of the open and close.
